The '''Budukhs''' ([[Budukh language|Budukh]]: –ë—É–¥–∞–¥, ''Budad'') are an ethnic group primarily from the mountainous village of [[Buduq]] in northwestern [[Azerbaijan]], one of the [[Shahdagh people|Shahdagh peoples]]. They speak the [[Budukh language]], which is a [[Northeast Caucasian languages|Northeast Caucasian language]] of the [[Lezgic languages|Lezgic branch]]. The [[Azerbaijani language]] is widely spoken.

The Budukh people are overwhelmingly [[Sunni Muslims]].

