{{Infobox prepared food | name = Caldo galego | image = Caldo gallego - juantiagues.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = | alternate_name = Caldo; Galician broth | country = [[Galicia (Spain)]] | region = | creator = Traditional | course = | type = [[Soup]] | served = Hot | main_ingredient = [[Cabbage]] or other greens, [[potato]]es, [[white bean]]s, fatty [[pork]] | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Caldo galego''' or simply '''caldo''' (in [[Galician language|Galician]]), also known as '''caldo gallego''' (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]), meaning literally '''Galician broth''', is a traditional soup dish from [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cooks.com/rec/search/0,1-0,caldo_gallego,FF.html|title=Caldo Gallego - Recipes |website=Cooks.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> It is similar to [[caldo verde]], popular in neighboring [[Portugal]].
Ingredients include ''repolo'' ([[cabbage]]), ''verzas'' ([[collard greens]]), ''[[Rapini|grelos]]'', or ''navizas'' (sweet [[turnip]] greens); potatoes; [[white bean]]s; and ''unto'' (lard). Additionally it can contain fatty pork, ''[[chorizo]]'', ham, or bacon (''compango'').
It is served hot as a starter, often as part of ''xantar'' (lunch), and sometimes dinner. Traditionally it was usually served in ''cuncas'' (earthen bowls).
==Variations== Depending on the availability of seasonal ingredients there are several variations: *'''Caldo branco''' includes chickpeas and beans. *'''Caldo chirlo''' or '''vigueiro''' *'''Caldo de casta√±as''' uses [[chestnut]]s
==See also== * [[Cabbage soup]] * [[Caldo verde]] * [[List of soups]] * [[Shchi]]
