{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Mauritius Tourism Promotion Authority |abbreviation = MTPA |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |formed = 1996 |preceding1 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Government of Mauritius]] |employees = |budget = |headquarters = [[Port Louis]], Mauritius |parent_agency = [[Ministry of Tourism and Leisure]] |child1_agency = |website = {{Url|http://www.tourism-mauritius.mu/}} |footnotes = }}
The '''Mauritius Tourism Promotion Authority''' (MTPA) is a statutory board under the [[Ministry of Tourism and Leisure]] of [[Mauritius]] established in 1996 by the MTPA Act. The task of the MTPA is to promote the country's [[tourism]] industry, provide information to tourists on facilities, infrastructures and services, to initiate action to promote cooperation with other tourism agencies, to conduct research into market trends and market opportunities and disseminate such information and other relevant statistical data on Mauritius.<ref name="MTPA">{{cite web|url=http://www.tourism-mauritius.mu/trade/en-uk/about|title=About the MTPA|publisher=Mauritius Tourism Promotion Authority|accessdate=24 November 2016}}</ref><ref name="gov">{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.mu/portal/site/tourist/menuitem.9e64aba61e45ea44c5e7931000b521ca/|title=Mauritius Tourism Promotion Authority|publisher=Government of Mauritius|accessdate=14 July 2012}}</ref>
